  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and proactive Accounts Executive to manage the company’s day-to-day accounting operations, ensuring accuracy and timeliness in financial processes that support business continuity and growth.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage accounts payable processes to ensure timely and accurate payments to vendors</li><li>Monitor accounts and proactively follow up on outstanding or overdue payments to optimize cash flow</li><li>Perform weekly and monthly bank reconciliations, ensuring accurate financial records and timely filing</li><li>Collaborate with team members to support ad-hoc accounting tasks and contribute to process improvements</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrated accounting experience of 1-2 years in relevant roles</li><li>Proficient use of Microsoft Excel to analyze and manage financial data</li><li>Certificate or Diploma in Accounting or an equivalent relevant certification</li><li>Strong attention to detail applied to financial data accuracy and organizational tasks</li><li>Effective time management skills to prioritize multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimal supervision while maintaining reliability and initiative</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Dependable team player with a proactive approach to problem-solving and continuous improvement</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Work schedule: 5 or 5½ day work week</li><li>Work location: Joo Chiat</li><li>Application instructions: Singaporeans and SPRs may send their updated resume with a recent photo and expected salary to [hrmingcoliving@gmail.com] with the subject line “Application – Accounts Executive.”</li></ul>",
